Sugarcane farmers have urged President Uhuru Kenyatta to retain Willy Bett as the Cabinet Secretary for Agriculture, Livestock and Fisheries.  The Kenya National Sugarcane Farmers Federation Secretary General Ezra Okoth said Bett should retain the seat in order to continue improving the sector.  The President is expected to fill the remaining cabinet slots after he unveiled a partial one two weeks ago. Read: Uhuru directs Cabinet Secretaries to prepare handover reports Speaking to journalists in Homa Bay town on Sunday, Okoth argued that Bett had initiated a lot of programmes aimed at improving sugarcane sector in the country.  "We appeal to President Kenyatta to reappoint Willy Bett in the same docket because his effort to improve sugarcane is commendable,” Okoth said.  The official said the CS had been holding talks with management of sugar milling companies to ensure sugarcane from farmers is milled on time.  “Bett has demonstrated commitments to ensure that sugarcane from farmers is harvested and taken to the factories at appropriate time,” he said. Okoth’s comments come at a time when uncertainty has gripped CSs who were not named in the partial Cabinet lineup.  On Saturday, COTU Secretary General Francis Atwoli urged Uhuru to name the remaining lot of CSs to quell growing anxiety in the country. Read: Wamalwa, Kiunjuri among 13 CSs in limbo after Uhuru retains six Click here for the latest political news